    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Linux LS command for Directories only]]></title>
    <link href="http://edmondscommerce.github.io/linux/linux-ls-command-for-directories-only.html"/>
    <updated>2012-01-10T12:58:31+00:00</updated>
    <id>http://edmondscommerce.github.io/linux/linux-ls-command-for-directories-only</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>If you have a large folder that contains a lot of files but you only want to see what directories are in there, then this little snippet is for you:</p>

<p>```</p>

<p>ls -d &mdash; */</p>

<p>```</p>

<p>You may decide to make an alias for it</p>

<p>```</p>

<p>echo &ldquo;alias lld=&lsquo;ls -alFhd &mdash; */&rsquo;&rdquo; >> ~/.bashrc</p>

<p>```</p>
]]></content>
